nnections between religious rhetoric and political dissent.Many of the sermons discussed were given during the rise of Islamic fundamentalism, and Gaffney attempts to describe this militant movement and to compare it with official Islam. Finally, Gaffney presents examples of the sermons, so readers can better understand the full range of contemporary Islamic expression.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aIslamxEgyptxEgypt. 0aIslamzEgypt. 0aIslam. 0aIslamic preachingzEgypt. 0aIslamic preaching. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Anthropology / Cultural & Social.2bisacsh  abuilding grassroots organizations.  acompares militant movement and official islam.  acontemporary islamic expression.  adeveloping leadership cadres.  afield research in egypt.  aforming public opinion.  amessage of islam.  amuslim preaching.  apolitical commentary.  apreacher and sermon.  areligious rhetoric and political dissent.  arise of islamic fundamentalism.  asocial history.  atheological sources.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of California Press Package Archive Pre-2000z97831106353480 cprintz978052008472840uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/9780520914582?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520914582423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780520914582/original  a978-3-11-063534-8  University of California Press Package Archive Pre-2000b2000  aEBA_EMB  aGBV-deGruyter-alles